      "comment": "ROCKY PACIFIC NZ (9) was returning from a spell last start when he raced parked but fought on well to finish second at Cranbourne. Draws on the back row but has won when second-up before so should be improved and was successful the only time he attempted this distance. MAAS BETTING AGAIN (3) showed plenty of fight to come from a wider barrier and score at the most recent appearance at Cranbourne, getting home by 1.4 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Primary contender. DRESSED IN GOLD NZ (10) could be close to a win after making it back-to-back placings by finishing third at Bendigo last time out. ULTIMATE JOY (4) resumes after 15 months but was readied with a series of trials and has shown ability in the past. Keep safe.",
